# Pull Request Process

## Before submitting a pull request

Please be sure that any install or build dependencies are removed before the end of the layer when doing a build.

### Checklist
Ensure that your `pull request` has followed all the steps below:

- [ ] Code compilation
- [ ] All tests passing
- [ ] Extended the documentation, if applicable
- [ ] Added myself to the CONTRIBUTORS file

### Description
For each `pull request`, please go into as much description as you can.

## Proposed changes
Describe why this pull request should be accepted. If it solves any previous requests, also link that issue.

### Types of changes
- [ ] New feature
- [ ] Bugfix
- [ ] So on...